{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "25", "m": "05", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "08", "M": "09", "S": "32"}}, "news": [{"title": "Puravankara acquires 14.57-acre land parcel in Mandur, Bengaluru", "para": "Puravankara has acquired a 14.57-acre land parcel in Bengaluru's Mandur, Budigere, with a potential gross development value of \u20b92,300 crore. This acquisition, comprising both purchased land and a joint development agreement, will yield approximately 1.8 million sq ft of saleable area. The company's Bengaluru developable landbank now stands at 25.61 million sq ft.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/puravankara-acquires-1457-acres-in-bengaluru-a-boon-for-real-estate-development/131304740?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-235538/131304740.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "No decision to dismantle LIFE Mission housing scheme: Kerala's LSG minister", "para": "Kerala's Local Self Government Minister K M Shaji has clarified that the UDF government has no plans to disband the LIFE Mission housing scheme. He stated that restoring powers to grama sabhas does not equate to scrapping the project, emphasizing that the new government aims to correct shortcomings rather than dismantle existing initiatives.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/local-self-government-minister-clarifies-no-plans-to-dismantle-life-mission-housing-project/131301044?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-13822/131301044.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Bihar government seeks \u20b91,600 crore from centre for rural housing", "para": "In a significant move to bolster rural development, Bihar has formally requested the Centre to disburse Rs 1,600 crore under the 'Mother Sanction' for the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana\u2013Gramin. With the state's Single Nodal Account running low, timely support for beneficiaries is at risk.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/bihar-government-requests-1600-crore-funds-for-rural-housing-initiative/131300972?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-273840/131300972.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Buildings across city on Kolkata civic body's bulldozer list", "para": "Kolkata's civic body has issued 48-hour demolition notices to several 'unauthorised' buildings in Tiljala and Beleghata, leaving residents in distress. Many bought flats believing them to be legal, only to face displacement. Developers have vanished, leaving residents scrambling for answers and fearing for their families as authorities target 'red zones' with widespread illegal constructions.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/kolkatas-civic-body-targets-thousands-of-illegal-buildings-for-demolition/131300134?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-39482/131300134.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "SRA cracks down on 219 rehabilitation buildings in Mumbai without OC", "para": "The SRA has issued notices to over 200 buildings lacking Occupancy Certificates (OC) that have been handed over to slum dwellers. This crackdown follows the state government's amnesty scheme, aiming to regularize such structures and address issues like lack of maintenance funds and developers forcing early possession.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/sra-takes-action-against-219-mumbai-rehabilitation-buildings-without-occupancy-certificates/131300038?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-75193/131300038.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Supreme court's rule on OCs delays smart meter rollout in Karnataka", "para": "Karnataka's smart meter rollout faced significant delays due to confusion over mandatory occupancy certificates. While aimed at modernizing the power sector, the Supreme Court's order stalled new connections, impacting lakhs of applications. Recent government intervention has accelerated installations, with over three lakh smart meters now in place, though challenges persist for many awaiting connections.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/supreme-courts-ruling-halts-smart-meter-rollout-in-karnataka/131300021?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-42298/131300021.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Municipality identifies 49 unsafe buildings in Mapusa", "para": "Mapusa authorities have identified 49 structurally unsound buildings, including 42 private and 7 government structures, within municipal limits. A joint re-inspection drive, ordered by the North Goa district collector, flagged these buildings as dangerous ahead of the monsoon.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/mapusa-identifies-49-dangerous-buildings-ahead-of-monsoon-to-ensure-public-safety/131290220?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-75290/131290220.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Bengaluru civic bodies' revenue drops under khata conversion scheme", "para": "Bengaluru's civic bodies face a projected revenue loss of nearly Rs 1,015 crore due to a fee reduction for converting B-khata to A-khata properties. The \"Nanna Khata Nanna Hakku\" campaign offers a 100-day window to regularize properties at a reduced 2% guidance value.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/bengaluru-civic-bodies-revenue-drops-under-khata-conversion-scheme/131290185?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-32468/131290185.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Drain-top buildings to face higher tax in Sambhajinagar; crackdown on direct sewage discharge", "para": "Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar municipal corporation will raise property taxes for buildings constructed over major drains. This move aims to tackle monsoon flooding and improve desilting operations. The civic body also ordered strict action against direct sewage discharge into stormwater drains. Enforcement drives will ensure properties connect to sewage treatment plants.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/sambhajinagar-to-enforce-higher-property-tax-on-drain-top-buildings-amid-sewage-crackdown/131290128?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-680157/131290128.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Dehradun cancels registration of 103 homestays violating rules", "para": "Dehradun district administration has cancelled registrations of 103 homestays for violating safety norms and operational guidelines. Inspections revealed commercialization, illegal bars, and lack of basic facilities, leading to the crackdown following a surge in criminal activities. The administration is also removing these properties from the state tourism website.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/hospitality/dehradun-shuts-down-103-homestays-for-safety-violations-amid-rising-crime/131299946?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-26282/131299946.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "hospitality"}, {"title": "Delhi to overhaul property registration system, modernise sub-registrar offices: CM", "para": "The Delhi government is preparing to completely overhaul the property registration system in the capital, aiming to make Sub-Registrar offices more modern, transparent and citizen-friendly, with a focus on eliminating delays, corruption and dependence on agents.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/delhi-government-revamps-property-registration-for-transparency-and-efficiency/131290075?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-40782/131290075.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Lucknow development body to redevelop dilapidated complex in Indira Nagar at \u20b9110 crore", "para": "Lucknow Development Authority (LDA) is set to redevelop the 40-year-old Kailashkunj Commercial Complex into a 13-storey mixed-use high-rise. The project, estimated at Rs 110 crore, will feature commercial spaces on lower floors and 3BHK residential flats above. Allottees will receive 1.25 times their current area in the new modern complex.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/lucknow-development-body-to-redevelop-dilapidated-complex-in-indira-nagar-at-110-crore/131289967?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-119992/131289967.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Illegal sand mining under lens as Chhattisgarh government steps up seizure drive", "para": "Chhattisgarh has intensified its crackdown on illegal sand mining with a recent seizure of heavy machinery and vehicles along the Jonk river. The state has also launched a toll-free helpline, 1800-233-2140, to empower citizens to report mining-related irregularities and strengthen surveillance across the state.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/allied-industries/chhattisgarh-government-cracks-down-on-illegal-sand-mining-amidst-environmental-concerns/131290241?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-191779/131290241.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "allied-industries"}, {"title": "Jharkhand building regularisation rules' amendment sought by technical professionals", "para": "Architects and engineers in Jharkhand are urging the Chief Minister to change new building regularization rules. Current rules exclude many people due to plot size limits. They propose using built-up area instead of total plot size. Road width requirements also prevent many older homes from qualifying. These changes aim to help more residents regularize their constructions.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/architects-demand-changes-to-jharkhand-building-regularisation-rules-to-protect-indigenous-rights/131290198?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-925329/131290198.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Jaipur: Ramganj building owner asked to raze tilted structure in 48 hour", "para": "A five-storey building in Jaipur's Ramganj has been declared unsafe and issued a 48-hour demolition notice by the Municipal Corporation. Residents had expressed panic and fear due to the visibly tilted structure, leading to vacated nearby houses and restricted movement. The corporation warned of demolition and cost recovery if the owner fails to act.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/urgent-action-required-jaipurs-tilted-building-owner-given-48-hour-demolition-notice/131290177?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1820874/131290177.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Fly ash continues to haunt Ennore residents", "para": "While the NGT had ordered the removal of fly ash deposited along the creek  river bed and the flood plains, roughly amounting to 56.7 lakh metric tonnes, and to plug the leaks in all pipelines that carry the ash slurry, a visit by TOI to Ennore and nearby hamlets revealed that the compliance by Tangedco has been subpar at best", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/fly-ash-crisis-in-ennore-residents-fight-for-health-and-clean-environment/131290024?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-234316/131290024.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "UDH notification sparks fear over commercialisation of residential areas in Jaipur", "para": "Jaipur's Urban Development and Housing department has permitted many commercial activities in residential areas. This decision sparks worry among planners and officials. They fear it will alter neighborhood character, increase congestion, and strain civic infrastructure. The move could lead to hotels and shopping complexes in residential lanes. This raises concerns about traffic, pollution, and essential services.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/udh-notification-sparks-fear-over-commercialisation-of-residential-areas-in-jaipur/131290005?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-23306/131290005.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}]}